Act exogenous labour productivity=
	0
	~	1
	~	Flag to determine exogenous labour productivity values
		0: endogenous
		1: from S Time exogenous lambda, fixed at the value it has in that timestep
		2: from S Time exogenous lambda, increasing at average growth rate of lambda in the \
		other sectors
		3: as 2 + number of workers reduced based on the increase in lambda (only \
		working if Act change gov consumption = 4,5 and Act Change baseline gov \
		consumption =6,7)
