Act income cap=
	0
	~	Dmnl
	~	Introduce a cap on disposable income of households.
		1 = nominal cap introduced at *S Time Policy start* at value *S income cap* and \
		staying fixed
		
		2 = nominal cap introduced at *S Time Policy start* at value of maximum households \
		income and decreasing linearly to *S income cap* at *S Time Shift End*
		
		3 = nominal cap introduced at *S Time Policy start* at value of disposable income of \
		*S income cap*th percentile (to be defined in equation which region \
		quintile corresponds) and staying fixed
		
		4 = nominal cap introduced at *S Time Policy start* at maximum value of households \
		disposable income and decreasing linearly to value *S income cap*th \
		percentile at *S Time Shift End* 
		
		       Note: for Act income cap = 3 OR 4, percentile corresponding to \
		value of *S income cap* has to be specified in equation for *effective \
		final income cap*, otherwise cap set to 0 as a control
	|

