Coefficient wage dispersion[female,ind,skill]=
	GET XLS CONSTANTS('?main', 'labour', 'wdispf')
	~	Dmnl
	~	This coefficient gives us the ratio between the standard deviation/average wages gis.
		One standard deviation is thus equal to the coefficient*average wage.
