constructed capacity investment initial[e techn]=
	constructed capacity investment initial MW[e techn]*MW to GW
	~	GW/Year
	~	Constructed capacity additions in 2010 by technology. Source: Jaxa-Rozen et al., \
		2022. For these initial values, we ignore depreciation, i.e. these values \
		are simply the difference between capacity 2011 and 2010 (max 0, since \
		linear depreciation of initial capital is assumed).
		Correction for autoproduction: scaled by non autoproduction shares using \
		Eurostat capacity by operator shares where available (i.e. solar,hydro, \
		wind) and Eurostat energy balance production shares by operator as proxy \
		for other technologies
	|

constructed capacity investment initial MW[e techn]=
	GET XLS CONSTANTS('?main', 'electricity', 'cap_constr_init*' )
	~	MW/Year
	~	Constructed capacity additions in 2010 by technology. Source: Jaxa-Rozen et al., \
		2022. For these initial values, we ignore depreciation, i.e. these values \
		are simply the difference between capacity 2011 and 2010 (max 0, since \
		linear depreciation of initial capital is assumed).
		Correction for autoproduction: scaled by non autoproduction shares using \
		Eurostat capacity by operator shares where available (i.e. solar,hydro, \
		wind) and Eurostat energy balance production shares by operator as proxy \
		for other technologies
	|

constructed storage investment initial[storage technologies]=
