]) ~~|
current capacity factor[e coal]= DELAY FIXED (
	expected capacity factor[e coal,e wind], Year 1, max capacity factor[e coal])
	~	Dmnl
	~	We introduce a delay here since the current values are used to plan \
		investment (i.e. future capital stock), i.e. they represent an \
		expectation. Thus, the delay represents the structure at the time of the \
		investment, i.e. time of production.
