	~	Dmnl
	~	Since the current values are used to plan investment (i.e. future capital stock), \
		i.e. they represent an expectation, we shift the lookup by one year. Thus, \
		production shares for 2011 are drawn in 2010 to plan production for 2011.
		Source: Eurostat energy balance considering only main activity producers, \
		exclude production by waste as this is allocated to sector E not D, The \
		sum is larger than 1 as storage discharge is included and all production \
		output is gross, i.e. there is double counting of this production.
	|

