Policy time increment=
	IF THEN ELSE(Time < S Time Policy start,
	             0,
	             IF THEN ELSE(S Time Policy start = S Time Shift end,
	                          1,
	                          min(1, (Time-S Time Policy start+1)/(S Time Shift end-S Time Policy start
	+1))
	)
	)
	~	1
	~	Used to calculate linear increases of policy paramaters. It has a value of:
		- 0 before S Time Policy start
		- 1 after S Time Shift end
		- If policy implemented over multiple years, it grows linearly from 0 in S Time \
		Policy start to 1 in S Time Shift end
		When policy is implemented in 1 year (S Time Shift end = S Time Policy \
		start), value of 1 in first year
