potential demand met=
	IF THEN ELSE(storage shortfall for max generation<1,
	
	(max generation/(1+current storage share of demand*storage shortfall for max generation
*(1-overall storage efficiency))
	)
	-(1-storage shortfall for max generation)*overall storage efficiency*current storage share of demand
*(max generation/(1
	+current storage share of demand*(1-overall storage efficiency))),
	
	(max generation/(1+current storage share of demand*(1-overall storage efficiency))))
	~	GW*Hour/Year
	~	if sufficient storage, generation technologies determine potential production
		if not enough storage, less production is channeled through storage, i.e. \
		there are less losses; but also demand that normally is met by storage \
		cannot be met. We assume storage production deficit (and reduction in \
		losses) are proportional to the actual vs require storage share
	|

potential demand met expected=
	IF THEN ELSE(expectedstorage shortfall for max generation<1,
	
	(expectedmax generation/(1+expected storage share of demand[batteries]*expectedstorage shortfall for max generation
*(1-expectedoverall storage efficiency
	)))
	-(1-expectedstorage shortfall for max generation)*expectedoverall storage efficiency
*expected storage share of demand[batteries]*(
	expectedmax generation/(1+expected storage share of demand[batteries]*(1-expectedoverall storage efficiency
))),
	
	(expectedmax generation/(1+expected storage share of demand[batteries]*(1-expectedoverall storage efficiency
))))
	~	Hours*GW/Year
	~		|

