priority elec[e techn]=
	1,3,5,6,6,2,6,6,4
	~	Dmnl
	~	We assume priorities are set to minimise emissions, i.e. first priorities \
		go to renewables (hydro, wind and solar), then comes nuclear followed by \
		nec (which includes bio and geothermal). Last come the fossil fuels ranked \
		from least dirty to dirtiest (i.e. gas, petroleum, coal).
	|

priority width=
	1
	~	Dmnl
	~	https://www.vensim.com/documentation/fn_allocate_by_priority.html
		"specifies how big a gap in priority is required to have the allocation go \
		first to higher priority with only leftovers going to lower priority.   \
		When the distance between any two priorities exceeds width and the higher \
		priority does not receive its full request the lower priority will receive \
		nothing."
	|

