External Data: all variables that import external data should be created in one of the three input views. Always use one of the "GET DIRECT" functions. 
12,0,0,164,301,159,98,3,135,0,11,-1,0,0,0,0-64-0,0-0-0,|12||0-64-0,0,0,0,0,0,0
Constants and parameters: should all be created in the inputs.parameters view. values should be entered directly in the model so that we can calibrate and vary then in sensitivity analysis. Whenever possible specify in the comments the data source and the identified range of variations for each parameters. All parameter values should also be kept in an external spreadsheet.
12,0,0,491,235,161,120,3,135,0,11,-1,0,0,0,0-64-0,0-0-0,|12||0-64-0,0,0,0,0,0,0
Naming convention: set Vensim with tools>options>setting>show_underbar and Model>settings>Sketch_use_hard_underbar. Use brief informative names and whenever necessary describe the variable in the comments. use the variable suffix to indicate its subscripts in alphabetical order: a=assets, c=cohorts, d=income categories, e=energy use of households, g=gender,h=household groups, i=industries, k=ind+fd+exp, l=ind+imp, n=energy source, p=coicope products, s=skill, t=time use, v=technologies, z=skill + capitalists. for exmaple labour demand by industry, skill and gender could be Lab_demand_gis.
12,0,0,491,409,161,47,3,135,0,11,-1,0,0,0,0-64-0,0-0-0,|12||0-64-0,0,0,0,0,0,0
Colors and shapes: All intermodule variables should be colored red. all policy variables orange and all indicators blue. Additionaly, important indicators should be inside an Hexagon
